assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Yamato Corporation engages in construction business in Japan. The company designs, constructs, and manages construction, civil engineering, air conditioning, sanitation, freezing, refrigerating, water supply, sewerage, water treatment, and hot bathing projects. Its project portfolio includes office and government buildings, stores, medical and welfare facilities, hotels, inns, leisure and hot spring facilities, food supermarkets, factories and warehouses, water and sewage, and water treatment facilities. The company was formerly known as Yamato Setsubi Kogyo K.K. and changed its name to Yamato Corporation in 2000. Yamato Corporation was founded in 1945 and is based in Maebashi, Japan.
